SIMPLE: wealthy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wealthy
<hw>Wealth"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Wealthier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Wealthiest</adjf>.]</amorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having wealth; having large possessions, or larger
than most men, as lands, goods, money, or securities; opulent; affluent;
rich.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>wealthy</qex> Hebrew of my tribe.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou broughtest us out into a <qex>wealthy</qex> place.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. lxvi. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, ample; full; satisfactory; abundant.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>wealthy</qex> witness of my pen.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wean</ent>⟦br⟧
